Subject: NTFS driver reports incorrect stats on 2.3.40
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2000/1/31/40

Hi all,
This might be old news, but I'll report it anyway. When mounting an NTFS partition with 2.3.40, "df" (GNU fileutils 4.0) reports incorrect values for size and Used (no, the disk isn't 40 GB):
Filesystem           1k-blocks      Used Available Use% Mounted on
/dev/hda5               804843    444155    319110  58% /
/dev/hda1               513808     13776    500032   3% /mnt/dos
/dev/hda7             39130304  37935280   1195024  97% /mnt/nt
The same if booted with 2.2.14:
df Filesystem           1k-blocks      Used Available Use% Mounted on
/dev/hda5               804843    444080    319185  58% /
/dev/hda1               513808     13776    500032   3% /mnt/dos
/dev/hda7              4891288   3696264   1195024  76% /mnt/nt
Cheers,
- Peter
